# cargo

Cargo is Rust's build tool and package manager. `build` compiles the crate;
`test` runs the test suite; `run` runs the default (or a named) binary; `check`
type-checks without producing artifacts (fast); `clippy` is the linter; `fmt`
rewrites formatting and `fmtcheck` verifies it without writing; `gate` is the
full pre-merge quality gate (fmt-check â†’ clippy-deny â†’ test â†’ build), exiting
non-zero on the first failure. For a Makefile project see @build/make.

| Recipe | Does |
|--------|------|
| `build` | compile the crate (default) |
| `test` | run the test suite (optional name filter) |
| `run` | run a binary (optional `bin` name, optional args) |
| `check` | type-check only, no codegen (fast feedback) |
| `clippy` | lint all targets, warnings denied |
| `fmt` | rewrite source to canonical formatting |
| `fmtcheck` | verify formatting without writing (CI/pre-commit) |
| `gate` | full gate: fmtcheck â†’ clippy â†’ test â†’ build |

`clippy` uses `--all-targets -- -D warnings` so a warning is an error (matching a
`[lints.rust] warnings = "deny"` crate). `fmtcheck` is the non-mutating fmt
variant. `gate` chains the four with `&&` so a red step aborts the rest. `release`
builds are not a separate recipe â€” pass `--release` is out of scope here; add it
later if needed.

```just
# compile the crate (default)
build:
  cargo build

# run the test suite (optional substring filter, e.g. test="wrap")
test filter="":
  cargo test {{filter}}

# run a binary (optional bin name + trailing args)
run bin="" args="":
  cargo run {{ if bin != "" { "--bin " + bin } else { "" } }} {{ if args != "" { "-- " + args } else { "" } }}

# type-check without producing artifacts (fast)
check:
  cargo check

# lint all targets with warnings denied (matches the project gate)
clippy:
  cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings

# rewrite source to canonical formatting
fmt:
  cargo fmt

# verify formatting without writing (exits non-zero if anything would change)
fmtcheck:
  cargo fmt --check

# full quality gate: fmt-check â†’ clippy (deny) â†’ test â†’ build
gate:
  cargo fmt --check && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo test && cargo build
```
